<center><font face='arial'><br><br>





 <h2>Controlling Your Pet</h2><br><br><br>Controlling your pet is vital to being a good mage, there are a few simple commands you need to know:<br><br><br><br>Firstly, tell it when to follow you:<br><br> <i>/pet follow me</i> - Tells the pet to follow you.<br><br> <i>/pet sit</i> - Tells the pet to stay where it is.<br><br> <i>/pet guard here</i> - Like /pet sit, except that the pet will always return to that position when its not fighting, until /pet follow me is used.<br><br><br><br>Now telling it to kill stuff:<br><br> <i>/pet kill</i> - Tells your pet to attack your current target.<br><br> <i>/pet back</i> - Tells your pet to back off and stop attacking.<br><br> <i>/pet hold</i> - THIS IS ONLY AVAILABLE AS THE RESULT OF AN AA ABILITY: Tells your pet to back off, and it will never attack unless specifically told to.<br><br><br>Other stuff:<br><br> <i>/pet health</i> - Your pet will tell you its health state.<br><br> <i>/pet who leader</i> - Your pet will say "My leader is <name>". Not very useful, but still.<br><br> <i>/pet get lost</i> - Dismisses your pet<br><br> <i>/pet taunt on</i> - Turns your pets taunting on<br><br> <i>/pet taunt off</i> - Turns your pets taunting off<br><br><br><br></center><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>Jaytee</b> says:</i><br><br>You forgot to mention pet back off will clear the pet's hate list.  Very important aspect of that command.<br><br><br><i><b>Dabrighter</b> says:</i><br><br>A table format might be better.

It also might be nice to list several example macro's and list the advantage of each.  

Information is still very basic.   Might expand on it and how it would be used.  

Example /Pet kill a black reaver will have it target the nearest a black reaver even if you can not click on it.  


<br><br><br><i><b>Antillas</b> says:</i><br><br>Well I feel oldschool.  Let's not forget '/pet as you were' which clears all aggro lists and all commands, leaving your pet to stand there virtually useless.  (For those of you who recall the days when pets didn't always back off...what do you mean they still don't?)<br><br><br><i><b>Antillas</b> says:</i><br><br>Oh, yes, more random tidbits.  You can hotkey your back off command to run several at once. Or to be informative to your group about what yoru targets are, who you're assisting, and who they had targeted at once.  If you learn a little about social scripting,  you can simply have your pet assist whichever group member you targeted with one button. (I do)  Ofcourse, I got bored enough to make it flashy, and even add animation to my /pet attack macro. <br><br><br><i><b>Erwyn</b> says:</i><br><br>fun little hotkey I have

/assist (main tank)
sick %t 
/pet attack

so it assists the main tank, handy with adds since your pet won't break mez.  May need to tell it to attack again if mob gets mezed by AoE mez if that's what enchie is using. It won't continue attacking once mez breaks.<br><br><br><i><b>Graccil</b> says:</i><br><br>You may also want to note that /pet hold does not clear your pets hate list as /pet back off does.  If you hold your pet then tell it to attack another, different mob, it will resume attacking the first.  Unless of course you /pet back off after /pet hold.

Oh and another little fun fact about /pet guard here, the pet will always face the direction of the nearest NPC, period.<br><br><br><i><b>Da_Yeto</b> says:</i><br><br>/pet who all leader

